This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with face image generation and editing. The use of deep neural networks also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) which are commonly used in graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
